trans-unit.source: Represents a collection of <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.ExpressionBuilder"></xref> objects.
This class cannot be inherited.
The ExpressionBuilderCollection class does not refer to any actual element in the underlying configuration file.
It is a construct that allows easy access to the compilation information it contains.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.ExpressionBuilderCollection"></xref> class.
Adds an <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.ExpressionBuilder"></xref> object to the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.ExpressionBuilderCollection"></xref>.
Adds an <xref:System.Web.Configuration.ExpressionBuilder> object to the collection.
If the assembly object is not initialized with assembly information, an exception is thrown.
If the assembly object already exists in the collection, the statement is ignored.
A string value specifying the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.ExpressionBuilder"></xref> reference.
The <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.ExpressionBuilder"></xref> object to add already exists in the collection, or the collection is read-only.
Clears all the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.ExpressionBuilder"></xref> objects from the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.ExpressionBuilderCollection"></xref> collection.

The <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.ExpressionBuilder"></xref> object at the specified index or <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""></xref> if there is no object at that index.
